$b = - $a; 

@which = ('first', 'second', 'third', 'fourth');
$tag1 = random(0,2,1);
$tag2 = random($tag1+1,3,1); 

@rc = ('rows', 'columns');
$tag3 = random(0,1,1);

BEGIN_TEXT

If the determinant of a \($n \times $n\) matrix \(A\) is \(\det (A)=$a\), and the matrix \(C\) is obtained from \(A\) by
swapping the $which[$tag1] and $which[$tag2] $rc[$tag3], then 
$BR
$BR
\(\det(C)= \) \{ans_rule(10)\}.  

END_TEXT

ANS(Compute($b)->cmp);
